\par 
\par Maternal grandfather - mother his eldest daughter \endash  was the poet, Jules Supervielle: son of a Montevideo banker in Uruguay, descended from earlier migrants from Oleron Ste Marie in B\'e9arn.  Family story of missing youngest brother \endash 
 elder brother died looking for him in Brazil \endash  given clocks and jewellery to set up the bank and succeed.  His younger brother \endash  father of Jules/Julio \endash 
 followed, but he and his wife died at sea and Jules brought up by uncle, and did not discover uncle was not his father until an older child.  Had not only the sensitivity to be a poet, but a big bank as support.  Does not remember much o}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid5988540 f him, visited him for tea, but }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572\charrsid4593572 
protected by his wife.  Died 1960/1. Not a model for Daniel.  Very good poetry, combines cosmic view with inner feeling.  Made most money from his Shakespeare translations.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid15663978\charrsid4593572 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572\charrsid4593572 The Banque Supervielle in Uruguay collapsed and disappeared in 1940, following the German occupation of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid15022078 
 France and rumours that is was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572\charrsid4593572 insolvent.  Still exists in Argentina, under other owners.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid15663978\charrsid4593572 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572\charrsid4593572 Maternal grandmother and wife of Jules was Pilar Sab
ela Cervantes-Isabella, from very upper class family in Argentina and Brazil, her Brazilian father Admiral Baroso.  One of 14, authoritarian mother.  Pilar used to protect Jules from noise of children, and if met him in the street, they were not supposed 
to bother him.  Jules died 1960/1, Pilar 1976, monument in cemetery at Oleron Ste Marie.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572 
