\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572\charrsid4593572 Pierre had a privileged childhood, onl
y child of parents in love.  Both parents teachers.  Thought of being a pianist.  Got very young into top school for intellectuals, Ecole Normale Sup\'e9
rieure, one of 30 in each year, historians, philosophers, classicists, etc.  Became friends with Raymond A
ron.  1927 went to Berlin, fell in love, back to France as Germanist.  Active political involvement with Front Populaire.  Civil servant in radio, education.  Back to Berlin with Aron 1933, saw burning of books, understood; hence when Germans came to Toul
ouse in 1942, they wanted him \endash  but saved by the concierge.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572 
