\f40\fs22\insrsid4593572\charrsid4593572  by good friend Nicolas Poulantzas (shared interest in Marx and women): very ambitious, led to his suicide.  Writing the book on holid
ay, August to November 1976, like a horse galloping for freedom.  Starts by examining classic social research on social mobility.  Then chapters on the family in different social classes: working class, shopkeepers, bourgeois, etc.  Then chapters on the f
ormation of the French working class, not written before; the power structure of the intellectuals (found that they all came through the Ecole Normale Sup\'e9rieur); on the top elite of rich bourgeois \endash  which again, sociologists had not studied 
\endash  those who own the media, go into politics and get help from state finances, etc (reactions of Poulantzas, Touraine).  In the end, fearing reprisals, dropped the chapter on the intelligentsia.  Regis Debray later wrote a good book on that.  }{
