The idea for the bakery project generated through meetings with students after May 1968.  Wanted to show the French public that France was still a class society by taking a familiar product: bread, or wine, shoes, 
automobiles, nylon stockings (proposed by a student who was a dancer: would lead to the chemical industry, planned obsolescence, women factory workers\'85)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid8261760 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572\charrsid4593572 For cars, very complex, capital and workers worldwide.  Fressinet has done it well.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid8261760\charrsid4593572 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572\charrsid4593572 Bread is much simpler, everyday product, produced by baker.  But made from flour, from wheat produced by rich capitalist peasantry in Paris basin \endash 
 could have gone into this.  Industrial and artisan bread.  Idea to tell the French public the share that workers and industri
al bakers and agrarian capitalists get from a loaf of bread.  Started interviewing bakery workers with student, Jacqueline Dufreyne: they told them about long hours, occupational illnesses, etc.  Tried to interview bakers but they refused, thought he was 
a tax inspector in disguise.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid8261760 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572\charrsid4593572   
\par Recorded about thirty bakery workers, mostly older but some apprentices.  Idea of saturation: enough interviews because the same stories were recurring \endash  of coming from a large family, apprenticeship to a provincial baker, at
 the end out of work so came to Paris industrial bakeries.  High demand because no Paris-bo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid5900228 rn worker would become a bakery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f40\fs22\insrsid4593572\charrsid4593572  worker.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572 
