Used an interview guide, internalised by each interviewer, with focus on labour, money, and structure of social relationships.  So strong theoretical orientation.  But at the same time the interview was non-directive.  The interview guide brief and inform
al, only ten or so questions.  As the interviews pr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid8814341 ogressed, the focus shifted: fr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572\charrsid4593572 
om how you become a baker, to health, competition between bakers.  So no fixed list of questions.  Objective is to build a model of the structure of relationships in bakery \endash  
workers, bakers, owners.  Using interviewees as informers from different situations \endash  rich/poor, older/younger, workers/bakers, etc.  Asks them because they are informed.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f40\fs22\insrsid4593572 
